Architecture / Interior Design office located in the NYC Flatiron District specializing in the design of contemporary high-end custom home interiors. We are currently seeking a professional candidate to work directly with principal who is passionate about contemporary interior design, self-motivated, capable of handling multiple projects efficiently with minimum supervision. Must be creative, innovative, highly detailed-oriented, and have excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.

Responsibilities:
• Perform leadership role designing projects in all phases of design, from programming to contract administration;
• Have a good understanding of interior finishes, materials, furniture, lighting, fixtures, and FF&E schedules and budgets for residential projects;
• Prepare presentation boards, AutoCAD drawings (including electrical & lighting plans), elevations, renderings, specifications, purchase orders and invoices;
• Manage the development of design from initial site measuring until final installations of FF&E;
• Visit job sites to address and resolve construction/installation issues;
• Schedule and conduct Client meetings to keep Clients current on proposed designs;
• Review submittals, shop drawings, substitutions and field conditions for conformance with design intent;
• Coordinate with outside team members such as contractors, vendors, workrooms and R&D companies;
• Track project tasks for multiple projects simultaneously; keep track of invoices, budget and timelines;
• Communicate with vendors, visit showrooms to select samples necessary for presentations.

Required Skills and Experience:
• 3-4 years post-graduate design experience with large experience working in high-end residential interiors projects;
• Bachelor's Degree in Interior Design or Architecture is a must. Master's Degree and/or NCIDQ are a plus;
• Proficiency in AutoCAD, REVIT, Photoshop and Sketchup;
• Excellent writing and communication skills;
• Excellent organizational and teamwork skills, with meticulous attention to detail;
• Must be proactive in anticipating Client questions;
• US Citizen or have a current work visa for work in the US

Salary: Competitive compensation commensurate with experience

Please Submit Resume and Work Samples


A growing start-up that develops and manufactures high end green prefabricated houses with innovative engineering systems and smart home technologies is seeking an experienced motivated assistant. 
Must be fluent with both Russian and English. Business background or understanding of architecture and engineering are plus.

We are looking for someone who can work independently and confidently under pressure. Creativity, resourcefulness, and multi-tasking skills are required.

The Personal Assistant will maintain a calm, relaxed presence while providing first-class operational oversight in a fast-paced and fast-moving environment. They embody solid communication skills and an eye for detail with a polished and professional style.

The candidate also must have a high level of discretion while maintaining a strong sense of urgency and sound judgment. This position requires the ability to anticipate the next steps, solve problems and be willing to take on anything to make the CEO’s life easier.

The candidate will also help us out with various projects related to the business, communicating with our engineering team and putting together the drawing, giving the drawings to the suppliers and manufacturers in order to get quotes for the materials; running errands, conducting research, creating presentations and preparing reports, organizing and maintaining files, answering and making calls as well as finding and communicating with other contractors that will take on new tasks in the organization.

Other duties as follows:
• Act as point of contact;
• Provide systematic and dependable follow-up;
• Handle confidential information with discretion.
Skills:
• A background or understanding of architecture or engineering is a big plus;
• Previous experience supporting executives;
• Knowledge and proficiency in the following software applications:
Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook.
• Strong written and verbal communication skills;
• Strong organizational skills;
• Ability to prioritize and multitask;
• Must have confidence;
• Great interpersonal skills including the ability to think and act strategically, provide sound judgment
• Highly resourceful team-player, with the ability to also be extremely effective independently.


This is a paid contract position with a test period that will last up to 3 months before hiring full time.
Applicants should be at least 18 years old and live within New York City. They also must be organized, fluent in English and Russian, and highly dependable. Interested applicants should send a resume and cover letter saying why you are the best candidate for this job. When sending your resume please write 'your full name for an assistant position' in the subject line of the email. We are looking forward to hearing from you!


Architects: 10-12 Years Experience

Architectural design firm based in Manhattan has immediate opening for suitably qualified, self-motivated architects having approx 10-12 years post graduate experience, primarily in residential architecture. 

Eligible candidates must have experience in the design and documentation of custom, high-end residential projects including landmarked townhouses, new homes and private estates and/or the renovation of existing structures. Prior experience with DoB Applications and with Landmarked or historic properties is a plus.  Candidate must be familiar with the NYC Building Code, should have excellent planning skills and, as well as knowledge of fine materials and their detailing.  

Acceptable candidates should have:
•	completed an architectural degree program;
•	approximately 10-12 years design and construction documentation experience;
•	prior experience with construction documentation for residential projects, including millworking;
•	extensive familiarity with New York City and New York State Building Codes;
•	AutoCAD (3D skills are a plus, but not mandatory);
•	US citizenship or established Visa / Work Permit.

E-mail professional resume with brief cover letter stating comparable experience only. Please note that resumes from recent graduates, over-qualified and/or overseas respondents will not be reviewed for this position.


